                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2638</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Sammons</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-02T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese naval authorities here have order Chefoo and Shanghai Naval vessels
                    proceed Chinwangtao be prepared to remove President Li if necessary. Tendency
                    here establish republic in south if monarchy restored in north.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sammons</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
